NAME
     true - Provides truth values

SYNOPSIS
     true

DESCRIPTION
   Purpose
     The true command tests for the appropriate status, true or
     false, before continuing or failing to continue in the
     execution of shell scripts.

EXAMPLE
     This command is typically used in input to sh(1) as follows:

          while true
          do
               command
          done

SEE ALSO
     false(1), sh(1).

DIAGNOSTICS
     True has exit status zero; false has exit status nonzero.


